YamlLocalization
===================

This is a plugin based on the rails localization plugin.

It uses YAML files (in RAILS_ROOT/lang/*.yml) instead of ruby code.

If it encounters missing translations, it will dump them into RAILS_ROOT/lang/add_me.yaml, unless you're running in production.


Example
=======

Using a language:

YamlLocalization.lang = 'en'

YAML example:

translations:
  - 'title':
    de: 'Titel'
    en: 'Title'


